ities. In an effort to broker peace in the woods, British Columbia’s NDP government launched a number of promising new forest policy initiatives in the 1990s. In Search of Sustainability brings together a group of political scientists to examine this extraordinary burst of policy activism. Focusing on how much change has occurred and why, the authors examine seven components of BC forest policy: land use, forest practices, tenure, Aboriginal issues, timber supply, pricing, and jobs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aForest management -- British Columbia. 0aForest managementzBritish Columbia. 0aForest policy -- British Columbia. 0aForest policyzBritish Columbia. 0aSustainable forestry -- Government policy -- British Columbia. 0aSustainable forestryxGovernment policyzBritish Columbia. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh1 aHoberg, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHowlett, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRayner, Jeremy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilson, Jeremy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485210440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774852104423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774852104/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British 